projects.description:
Business Consultant with the role of Scrum Master, responsible for a successful implementation of ServiceNow for DPG Media. This concerned a clone of the current Sanoma ServiceNow instance (due to takeover by DPG) on which all irrelevant data is deleted and the new data and configurations were added. 

Sections of the implementation:
Service Portal, Service Catalog, Service Level Management, Service Request Management, Incident Management, Problem Management, Change Management, Configuration Management, Knowledge Management, several integrations with external systems.

Jessica’s responsibilities:
- Facilitate Scrum Team;
- Advise and guide/support the Product Owner at the customer end;
- Coordinate clone and data activities;
- Plan and execute workshops and prepare stories for the Sprint;
- Configure ServiceNow;
- Coordinate with and report to customer management;
- Planning and providing a demo containing all functionalities at the end of the Sprint;

Business Consultant with the role of Scrum Master, responsible for a successful implementation of ServiceNow for PARK NOW. This concerned a rebuild of the current ServiceNow instance on Madrid to a new ServiceNow instance on New York. 

Sections of the implementation:
Service Portal (IT and CSM), Service Catalogus (IT and CSM), Service Level Management, Service Request Management, Incident Management, Problem Management, Time registration, GRC, Audit and Security Incident. Implemented several integrations with Jira. 

Jessica’s responsibilities:
- Facilitate Scrum Team;
- Advise and guide/support the Product Owner at the customer end;
- Plan and execute workshops and prepare stories for the Sprint;
- Coordinate with and report to customer management;
- Planning and providing a demo containing all functionalities at the end of the Sprint;

Business Consultant, responsible for the implementation of all requirements and maintenance of the backlog of the Quint Technology ServiceNow instances. As Technical Consultant partly responsible for the configuration of these requirements. Coordination of the maintenance and development of all Impulse4 releases (QT implementation product to accelerate implementations) also lies within the responsibilities of the development team, including training new employees in the area of ServiceNow and Impulse4. If extra capacity is needed, assist the Support department including temporary assignments on customer projects.
My responsibilities:
•	Development and maintenance of the Quint Technology backlog (own ServiceNow instances);
•	Development and maintenance of the Impulse4 backlog for all Impulse4 releases;
•	Assist the Support department when needed;
•	Train new employees in the areas of ServiceNow and Impulse4.

Business Consultant with the role of Scrum Master and Technical Consultant, responsible for a successful implementation of ServiceNow IT Service Management and Project & Portfolio Management. In the role of Business Consultant/Scrum Master responsible for the gathering of all requirements through workshops and backlog refinement. In the role of Technical Consultant responsible for the translation of requirement to functionalities and the configuration of those functionalities, supported by the implementation accelerator Impulse4.
Jessica’s responsibilities:
•	Advise and guide/support the Product Owner at the customer end;
•	Plan and execute workshops and prepare stories for the Sprint;
•	Translate requirements to functionalities and configure these functionalities;
•	Planning and providing a demo containing all functionalities at the end of the Sprint;
•	Implement all configurations on the Production instance.

